<subSubSection pageId="710" pageNumber="711" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">
This species is known from northeastern Arkansas (Kraim 1983: 137, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1884" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Selenophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpolitus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Selenophorus perpolitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Amite County in southwestern Mississippi (Peter W. Messer pers. comm. 2012), East Baton Rouge Parish in southern Louisiana (Igor Sokolov pers. comm. 2009), and from southern Texas (Johnson 1978: 68; Zapata, Live Oak, and Uvalde Counties, CMNH) to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yucatán">Yucatan</normalizedToken>
(Putzeys 1878: 65).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="710" pageNumber="711" type="records">
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">USA</emphasis>
: AR, LA, MS, TX - Mexico
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="710" pageNumber="711" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="710" pageNumber="711">
The systematic position of this species is not quite settled. It was transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Athrostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Athrostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Erwin [in Reichardt 1977: 428, under the spelling 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Athrostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Athrostictus punculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Putzeys, 1878)]. It was retained in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Selenophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Selenophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Noonan (1985: 41) although he did not study specimens. Bates (1891a: 243) wrote &quot;the species [i.e., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1878" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Selenophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Selenophorus punctatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] belongs to a group of the genus in which the thorax (except on the disk) and the elytra are closely punctured, a group which connects 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Selenophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Selenophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Arthrostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="710" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="710" pageNumber="711">Arthrostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[sic].&quot;
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
